DPS: 3 Shield
Power Use: 1.3W        ROF: 3.3/s
Suck Weapon: 67        Suck Afterburner: 50"

1436, "(fr)The Leech Cannon depletes the power supply of enemy fighters. Use it to disable afterburners, energy weapons, and shields. No subsystems targeting is required, just point and shoot.

The Leech Cannon is an anti-fighter weapon with minimal effect against larger vessels."

1437, "(fr)Shield Breaker"

1438, "GTW-99 Brise-Bouclier"

1439, "(fr)EM Cannon
Velocity: 400        Range: 1600
DPS: 133 Shield
Power Use: 0.7W      ROF: 3.3/s"

1440, "(fr)Developed as an anti-Shivan weapon, the Shield Breaker inflicts massive damage to enemy defensive systems. This weapon causes no structural damage, but coupling it with an anti-hull cannon is very effective against larger Shivan bombers such as the Seraphim."

1441, "D-Advancé"

1442, "(fr)GTW-41X Advanced Disruptor"

1443, "(fr)Penetrator - Destroys Subsystems
Velocity: 575        Range: 863
DPS: 42 Shield, 42 Subsystem
Power Use: 1.3W      ROF: 1.7/s"

1444, "(fr)The Advanced Disruptor Cannon is much like the GTW-41 Disruptor. However, its speed and higher subsystems damage make it much more useful in operations against faster moving targets."

1445, "Canon Électrique"

1446, "GTW-65 Canon Électrique"

1447, "(fr)High-Velocity Cannon
Velocity: 1000       Range: 1500
DPS: 15 Hull, 15 Shield, 15 Subsystem
Power Use: 2.5W      ROF: 0.5/s"

1448, "(fr)A GTI prototype cannon, the Railgun was originally developed as an attempt to penetrate the shields of the Lucifer superdestroyer. The weapon uses a series of electromagnets firing with millisecond precision to accelerate caseless uranium slugs at extreme velocity. While its range, accuracy, and impact force are the highest in the Terran arsenal, shield damage is low and the weapon suffers from an extended recharge cycle. Although the Railgun is technically a ballistic weapon, the slugs are extremely small, and for tactical purposes the quantity of ammunition is practically unlimited."

1449, "MX-50"

1450, "GTM MX-52"

1451, "(fr)Standard Missile, Passive
Velocity: 150        Range: 1500
Damage: 25 Hull, 10 Shield, 25 Subsystem
Fire Wait: 0.75s     Reload: 16/s"

1452, "Convient à toutes les batailles spatiales - défensives et offensives - charge utile moyenne (16,5 Kt) - guidage infrarouge et ciblage semi-intelligent - le pilote choisit la cible souhaitée, et le MX-50 suit la cible choisie en fonction de l'émission de chaleur provenant du moteur, des compartiments d'armes et du cockpit du vaisseau cible - le MX-50 attaquera toujours une cible déterminée comme hostile par l'ordinateur de bord de tout vaisseau de combat de la GTA, assurant ainsi un taux de mortalité plus élevé, si le pilote se trouve dans une situation de combat intense où il pourrait être difficile de viser avec précision.

Les premières expériences avec des défenses à base d'énergie, comme le réseau de déflecteurs de Ross 128, ont montré que cette arme est extrêmement faible contre tout ce qui n'est pas à base d'acier."

1453, "Missile-D"

1454, "GTM-31 Missile Disrupteur"

1455, "(fr)Disruptor - Fast Lock-On
Velocity: 80        Range: 1200
Damage: 1 Subsystem
Fire Wait: 5s        Reload: 0.8/s
Shut Down Ships for 2-8 Seconds"

1456, "(fr)Advanced signal processing - high precision interception capability - small payload (9 Kt), combining both conventional explosives and a localized blast of energy caused by the effect of impact upon the laser-propulsion system of the missile - designed to temporarily disable subsystems on hostile targets.

The D-Missile is designed to temporarily stop a cruiser or destroyer from firing its laser turrets. The effect will last about 10 seconds per missile fired, so using these to temporarily disable a cruiser should usually be for suppression until the cruiser is destroyed, or whatever was trying to evade the cruiser has gotten out of range. Only a few ships can carry these - and they are very scarce - so proper utilization is important."

