1458, "GTM-3 Missile Furie"

1459, "
Roquette Non-Guidée
Vitesse : 300             Portée : 900
Dégâts : 30 Coque, 15 Bouclier, 18 Sous-Système
Délai : 0.3s       Rechargement : 48/s"

1460, "Petits missiles non-guidés à tir rapide - tirés en essaims - les chasseurs de la GTA peuvent emporter plus de missiles Furies que de missiles conventionnels, en raison de leur petite taille - utilisés pour la distraction et d'autres mesures tactiques - et de leur très faible charge utile (3 Kt).

Leur utilisation est recommandée dans les situations de combat rapproché et contre des cibles plus importantes où la poursuite n'est pas un problème."

1461, "Intercepteur" ; The #Missle addition is needed for differentiation to the ship type of the same name.

1462, "GTM-9 Intercepteur"

1463, "
Missile de Combat, Verrouillage Rapide
Vitesse : 250            Portée : 1250
Dégâts : 150 Coque, 120 Bouclier, 75 Sous-Système
Délai : 2s          Rechargement : 8/s"

1464, "(fr)All-aspect seeking - laser tracking senses energy reflected off a target from the primary weapon systems of the target, increasing single-pass kill probability - medium payload (18.5 Kt) - missile is designed to pierce reinforced hull, thus securing itself to the target, prior to detonating (15 ms delay).

This is the standard issue fighter killer in the GTA. Designed to take out fighters with minimum hassle, a simple lock is all that is needed to grab the enemy's attention. Short lock time, good speed, and decent payload makes this the best missile to use against all but the strongest ships. Its effectiveness against large targets, however, is less than a typical laser run, making this primarily a ship-to-ship missile."

1465, "Phénix V"

1466, "GTM Phénix V"

1467, "(fr)Heavy Missile, Slow Lock-On
Velocity: 175        Range: 1750
Damage: 350 Hull, 175 Shield, 280 Subsystem
Fire Wait: 5s        Reload: 1.3/s"

1468, "(fr)All-aspect seeking - same tracking system as the Interceptor - large payload (50 Kt), but slower than the Interceptor - one of the best fire-and-forget missiles ever developed - many fighter pilots within the GTA regard the Phœnix V as the weapon of choice against high value, heavily defended targets.

The number one bomber killer in our arsenal, this is the single most damaging missile that can be equipped on a fighter craft. The longer lock time and slower speed make it less of a dogfight weapon and more of an anti-bomber warhead. Its extra damage against shields makes it especially useful against the Shivan bombers."

1469, "Synaptique"

1470, "GTM-1 Bombe Synaptique"

1471, "(fr)Anti-Fighter Weapon, Unguided, 15 Submunitions
Velocity: 90         Range: 225
Damage: 60 Hull, 45 Shield, 60 Subsystem
Submunition: 525 Hull, 525 Shield, 263 Subsystem
Fire Wait: 5s        Reload: 0.4/s"

1472, "(fr)Missile propulsion unit carrying several small intelligent $quotebomblets$quote - when distance to target is less than 100 m or when time to impact is less than 2 sec., bomblets direct missile to the most vulnerable part of the ship of those parts of the ship facing the missile - bomblets then separate from missile propulsion unit and form a sphere - inertia continues to carry bomblets in the direction of the target - the missile propulsion unit continues to advance toward the target - when the missile hits the target or 1.5 seconds after the missile should have hit the target, the bomblets explode - the spherical shape of the formation of the bomblets helps to ensure a fairly even level of damage across a sensitive area on the target - the spherical shape also ensures that the target will not be able to effectively maneuver away from the blast, thus ''pinning'' the target to a specific area in space - can also act as dumbfire - medium payload per bomblet (15 Kt) - very small payload for missile (2 Kt).

Nicknamed the $quoteEarthshaker$quote by the bomber pilots who tested this, it is a bomber's best defense against fighters. The Synaptic Bomb can do a lot of damage to a lot of ships at one time."

